 Dutywa - Dutywa police are investigating a case of culpable homicide and failure to stop after an accident. "It is alleged that a female pedestrian was hit by a motor vehicle along the N2 Road, near Dothi Village, Dutywa," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "The fatal accident took place on Monday, 08 June 2020 at about 18:00. "The vehicle that hit the deceased did not stop." He added that the deceased has not yet been identified. "Any family that is looking for a relative is urged to contact Dutywa Police on 047 489 1333." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 